                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/372: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-08T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 8, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. For Braden. Your 23, February 7, 4 p.m. The War Department authorizes the
                    designation of Captain Sharp with the understanding <pb facs="0141" n="42"
                        xml:id="pg_42"/> that his work on the commission shall not interfere with
                    his departure from Buenos Aires upon the termination of his duties as Military
                    Attaché.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
